SPS) models, a weaker AC variant\nthat artificially shuts off cooling and star formation at z=2 yields the same\nstellar mass as the un-contracted models. For these reasons, we believe our\nX-ray analysis prefers this weaker AC variant applied to either an NFW or\nEinasto DM halo. Finally, the BCG stellar mass strongly favors SPS models with\na Chabrier or Kroupa IMF over a Salpeter IMF. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 25 Nov 2016 21:00:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-18"}
