 in the corrected data. The NNBR\nand PLD methods consistently minimize both white and red noise levels and\nshould be considered reliable and consistent. The planets in this study span\nequilibrium temperatures from 1100 to 2000~K and have brightness temperatures\nthat require either high albedo or efficient recirculation. However, it is\npossible that other processes such as clouds or disequilibrium chemistry may\nalso be responsible for producing these brightness temperatures.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 26 Nov 2016 13:24:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-12-28"}
